—Щbarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2023-08-23-happy-birthday-nushell-4.mdЩ@26641035e524c985d43387514911a63b9e9ab4d37d5457a97471841c6c5f961fЩ%title: Celebrating 4 years of Nushell‘Щ2Surprise, we support script subcommands (sophiajt)Ъ’"Turns out, we already support subcommands in scripts."
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
# adds 100 to the argument
def "main foo" [
  x: int # the amount to start with
] {
  print ($x + 100)
}

def "main" [] {
  print "usage: maintest.nu <command name>"
}

```
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> nu ../maintest.nu foo 123
223

```
It even comes with its own help

automated help generated for the script subcommand
